==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monogamous
<hw>Mo*nog"a*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>monogamus</ets> having but one wife, Gr. <?/; <grk>mo`nos</grk>
single + <?/ marriage.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Upholding, or practicing,
monogamy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Monogamian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Mating with but one of the
opposite sex; -- said of birds and mammals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>monogamousness</ent>⟦br⟧
